The paper deals with optimal control of a distributed system subject to communication delays and power constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of linear quadratic Gaussian (LQG) control, which is a common technique in control theory and is likely to be associated with the Machine Learning (cs.MA) sub-category. The paper also involves information theory, as it deals with information-constrained control, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of decomposition techniques to solve the problem suggests that the paper may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
